refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
resourceoci_parse resourceconnection stringquery
Prepares the queryusing connection and returns the statement identifier, which can be used with oci_bind_by_name, oci_execute and other functions.

&reftitle.notes;
This function does not validate query. The only way to find out if query is valid SQL or PL/SQL statement - is to execute it.
In PHP versions before 5.0.0 you must use ociparse instead. This name still can be used, it was left as alias of oci_parse for downwards compatability. This, however, is deprecated and not recommended.
